<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session  
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>The human rights of migrants:  draft President&#8217;s statement 
</b></p>
<p> The Human Rights Council takes note of the High-level Dialogue on Migration and 
Development held by the General Assembly on 14 and 15 September 2006, in particular of the 
relevance given to the human rights of migrants,  
</p>
<p> The Human Rights Council emphasizes the need to address the human rights dimension 
of migration in a comprehensive manner, in particular the promotion and protection of the 
human rights of all migrants, and to that end shall pursue this issue in its upcoming sessions.  
</p>
